RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE PROCESS vied three wide, then two wide while in the three path into the turn, showed the way narrowly between horses around the bend as an outer rival joined the fray, repelled that one entering the lane, drove clear of his inner counterpart at the furlong grounds before shifting ground outwardly inside of that station, straightened course and held sway. SHAKIN LOOSE prompted along the inside early on, backed off to stalk approaching the turn, pursued from the two path around the bend, chased behind the leader entering upper stretch, but shifted out while pursuing that one inside the final furlong, bumped an outer rival at the sixteenth pole as his rider lost his crop and ran on late to secure place. SEARCY broke outwardly at the start, tracked four wide, advanced to press the top pair from the four path entering the turn, bid turning for home, but gave way entering the lane, chased among foes entering the final furlong, but was bumped by an inner rival into an outer foe at the sixteenth pole and steadied in crowded quarters in the process. BURGUNDY ROYALE hopped slightly before exchanging contact with an outer rival at the start, vied two wide and between horses early on, cleared an inner rival and battled with a pair of outer rivals turning for home, sustained pressure through upper stretch but gave way in the final furlong. STORMIN LOVE chased three wide and between horses early on, but faded in the five path at the three furlong pole. FOLLOWING A STEWARDS' INQUIRY REVIEWING THE FINAL FURLONG, SHAKIN LOOSE WAS DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED FIFTH.
